CNBC for decades."}, "profile_description_language": "en", "profile_image_shape": "Circle", "relationship_perspectives": {"blocked_by": false, "blocking": false, "followed_by": false, "following": false, "muting": false}, "rest_id": "1394971", "super_follow_eligible": false, "super_followed_by": false, "super_following": false, "verification": {"verified": false}}}}, "edit_control": {"edit_tweet_ids": ["2044848109117722856"], "editable_until_msecs": "1776368355000", "edits_remaining": "5", "is_edit_eligible": true}, "grok_analysis_button": true, "is_translatable": false, "legacy": {"bookmark_count": 1, "bookmarked": false, "conversation_id_str": "2044848109117722856", "created_at": "Thu Apr 16 18:39:15 +0000 2026", "display_text_range": [0, 273], "entities": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [0, 5], "text": "OPTX"}, {"indices": [90, 95], "text": "CIEN"}], "timestamps": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "favorite_count": 12, "favorited": false, "full_text": "$OPTX 2 o'clock balloon comment. If you started a bit in Syntec Optics, notice Ciena.. as $CIEN move up by several X.. well, photonics is what relatively unknown OPTX does.. to connect photonically. And Syntec Optics is in space, data-centers and weapons.. optical photonic", "id_str": "2044848109117722856", "is_quote_status": false, "lang": "en", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 1, "retweet_count": 0, "retweeted": false, "user_id_str": "1394971"}, "note_tweet": {"is_expandable": true, "note_tweet_results": {"result": {"entity_set": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [0, 5], "text": "OPTX"}, {"indices": [90, 95], "text": "CIEN"}, {"indices": [476, 481], "text": "OPTX"}, {"indices": [671, 677], "text": "OPTXW"}, {"indices": [796, 801], "text": "AMZN"}, {"indices": [1154, 1159], "text": "ONDS"}, {"indices": [1161, 1166], "text": "QBTS"}, {"indices": [1199, 1204], "text": "BBAI"}, {"indices": [1272, 1276], "text": "RDW"}, {"indices": [1555, 1560], "text": "IONQ"}, {"indices": [1586, 1591], "text": "QBTS"}], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNDQ4NDgxMDg5MjA1Njk4NTc=", "media": {"inline_media": []}, "richtext": {"richtext_tags": []}, "text": "$OPTX 2 o'clock balloon comment. If you started a bit in Syntec Optics, notice Ciena.. as $CIEN move up by several X.. well, photonics is what relatively unknown OPTX does.. to connect photonically. And Syntec Optics is in space, data-centers and weapons.. optical photonic connectivity. 

Let's see what it can doing in the weeks and months ahead... notably tightly controlled by one man (the CEO) and has Warrants that have to trade over $18 for 20 consecutive days before  $OPTX can call them in (very important); so I imagine the buyer of common expects to see the common move to 18 or higher (typically such deals go 10-30% above the conversion level at least); and $OPTXW (the Warrants would go anywhere from 4 to 10.. depending how high OPTX goes. We'll see, but with Anduril and Amazon ( $AMZN ) likely involved (one for the U.S. Army and the other for the Kuiper satellite LEO -low earth orbit- program) .. I imagine OPTX moves higher rapidly at some point. Zero analyst coverage; so that encourages me that the real action is ahead. It's just one of the newer picks this year; and doesn't at all distract from others we like, hold or follow... $ONDS, $QBTS (very strong in Quantum now) or $BBAI (seems to be positioning for a move.. finally if it happens). 

Or $RDW and others.. our diversified picks are mostly within what I broadly call 'Global Defense, Security & Drones' (but let's include space as part of that); and n that sense we are concentrated in what 'serious' money is now more interested in than old-guard big-caps. Starting with $IONQ (sold for good gain) and $QBTS (sold Warrants kept common) back in 2025; we added ONDS and others along the way. We embraced this overall theme well before others and patienly fought through ups-and-downs and believe highs are ahead not beyind for virtually all of these. My humble opinion."}}}, "rest_id": "2044848109117722856", "source": "<a href="https://mobile.twitter.com" rel="nofollow">Twitter Web App</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "1359", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}
